            <creation>This story, with the short title "Gift of a Luminous White Cloth," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around <date>1800</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>A man who loved and devoted himself to Mary recounted a vision he had one night in which a man in a luminous robe appeared to him. This mysterious man gave the dreamer his gleaming white garment and told him to write down the miracles of Mary—presumably, on this very robe. When he woke up, the man immediately composed a prayer of praise for Mary.</p>
